          },
          "pause": true,
          "displayType": "poster",
          "buttonOnMobile": false,
          "label": "<p>What do Weibel-Palade bodies in endothelial cells store?</p>",
          "x": 30,
          "y": 30,
          "width": 40,
          "height": 25,
          "libraryTitle": "Multiple Choice",
          "action": {
            "library": "H5P.MultiChoice 1.16",
            "params": {
              "question": "<p>What do Weibel-Palade bodies in endothelial cells store?</p>",
              "answers": [
                {
                  "text": "<div>Nitric oxide and endothelin</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Nitric oxide is a gas synthesised and released on demand by endothelial cells — it cannot be stored in membrane-bound organelles. Endothelin is similarly produced as needed.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Type IV collagen and laminin</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Type IV collagen and laminin are structural components of the basement membrane, produced by endothelial cells and pericytes. They are deposited extracellularly, not stored in Weibel-Palade bodies.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>von Willebrand factor and P-selectin</div>",
                  "correct": true,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Weibel-Palade bodies store von Willebrand factor, essential for platelet adhesion and coagulation, and P-selectin, which mediates the initial tethering of leukocytes to the endothelium during inflammation.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Actin filaments and vimentin</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Actin microfilaments and vimentin intermediate filaments are cytoskeletal components distributed throughout the endothelial cell cytoplasm. They are not stored in Weibel-Palade bodies.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                }
              ],
              "overallFeedback": [
                {
                  "from": 0,
                  "to": 50,
                  "feedback": "Weibel-Palade bodies store von Willebrand factor and P-selectin. vWF is essential for platelet adhesion in coagulation, while P-selectin mediates leukocyte tethering during inflammation — both critical ultrastructural details of endothelial cells."
                },
                {
                  "from": 51,
                  "to": 100,
                  "feedback": "Correct. Weibel-Palade bodies are distinctive endothelial organelles storing von Willebrand factor (for coagulation) and P-selectin (for leukocyte recruitment), released by exocytosis when the endothelium is activated."
                }
              ],
